Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Application
    The Application class represents the entry point for running the game application.
    AreaController
    The AreaController class manages the control flow for the game's areas and encounters.
    AreaModel
    The AreaModel class represents the game area where the player moves and encounters creatures.
    AreaOptionsView
    The AreaOptionsView class represents the graphical user interface for selecting different game areas.
    AreaView
    The AreaView class represents the graphical user interface for displaying and navigating game areas.
    BattlePhaseController
    The BattlePhaseController class handles the user interactions in the battle phase of the game.
    BattlePhaseModel
    The BattlePhaseModel class represents the game logic for the battle phase, managing interactions between the player's active creature and the enemy creature.
    BattlePhaseView
    The BattlePhaseView class represents the graphical user interface for the battle phase of the game.
    Controller
    The Controller class serves as the base class for various controllers in the application.
    CreatureView
    The CreatureView class represents the view for displaying information about creatures in the game.
    Driver
    The Driver class contains the main method to run the application.
    EvolutionController
    The EvolutionController class is responsible for handling user input and updating the EvolutionView and EvolutionModel accordingly.
    EvolutionModel
    The EvolutionModel class represents the model for creature evolution in the game.
    EvolutionView
    View class for the evolution screen, extending the InventoryView.
    InventoryBPController
    Controller class for managing the inventory during the battle phase.
    InventoryController
    Controller class for managing the inventory and its interaction with views during various phases.
    InventoryModel
    The Inventory class represents a collection of creatures that a player can carry.
    InventoryView
    View class representing the inventory display, allowing users to manage and view their creatures.
    MessageView
    View class representing a message display to communicate information or instructions to the player.
    OptionsController
    Controller class responsible for handling user interactions in the OptionsView.
    OptionsView
    View class responsible for displaying the Options menu.
    StartController
    Controller class responsible for handling user interactions in the start phase of the game.
    StartViewOne
    View class representing the first screen of the game.
    StartViewTwo
    View class representing the second screen of the game where players choose their starter POKIMON.
    View
    A base class representing a view in the application's user interface.
